This is the final submission of my master thesis that is hosted on Concordia&rsquo;s Spectrum repository here. It explores online kernel change point detection methods across a variety of synthetic datasets. Real market liquidity data is also analyzed using a kernel change point method.
To cite this thesis use the following bibtex snippet:
@unpublished{library987140, year = {2020}, month = {August}, author = {Tyler Manning-Dahan}, title = {Applying Kernel Change Point Detection To Financial Markets}, school = {Concordia University}, url = {https://spectrum.library.concordia.ca/987140/} }
